text.section:
In investigating a written complaint made under this section, the Commissioner may:
Hold a hearing on the complaint at a time and place in this State that are reasonably convenient to the parties involved;
Subpoena witnesses;
Take depositions of witnesses who reside outside of this State in the same manner as provided for depositions to be taken in civil actions in courts of record;
Pay witnesses the same fees and mileage for their attendance as provided for witnesses in civil actions in courts of record; and
Administer oaths.
